HCR NO. 94 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, the Legislature of Louisiana wants to be sure that establishing an
individualized standard for boating safety compliance stops and checks does not have
negative impacts to the safety of Louisiana citizens on the water.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
urge and request the Louisiana Department of Wildlife and Fisheries to provide annual
boating safety compliance reports to the House Committee on Natural Resources and
Environment and the Senate Committee on Natural Resources at least thirty days prior to the
convening of the Regular Session of the Legislature containing the following information:
(1) The number of boating incidents.
(2) The number of boating fatalities.
(3) The number of boating safety related stops.
(4) The number of citations issued at stops.
(5) The number of vessels registered in the state.
(6) State expenditures on the boating safety program.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
secretary of the Louisiana Department of Wildlife and Fisheries.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
